      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im lookin at a 2018 camry throwin a p0171 code. checked the maf sensor and it seems fine, so i dont think the air intake measurement is the issue. what else should i be lookin at for a lean condition?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A lean condition, like a misfire in a car, can be caused by a few different issues. Since your maf sensor seems fine, you might want to check the fuel pressure. A low fuel pressure can cause a lean condition, and you might want to check the fuel pump and fuel filter for clogs or damage. Also, check the fuel injectors to make sure they're opening properly and delivering the right amount of fuel. If the injectors are clogged or malfunctioning, they might not be delivering enough fuel, causing a lean condition. You might also want to check the oxygen sensor, as a faulty sensor can cause incorrect readings and lead to a lean condition. Lastly, check the spark plugs and ignition system, as a weak spark can also cause a lean condition. If you're still having trouble, you might want to consult a professional mechanic. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
