      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i aint sure about the fuel pump yet. what about vacuum leaks though? could a leak in a vacuum hose cause this same p0171 code on this engine?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, a vacuum leak could definitely cause a lean condition and trigger the P0171 code. Vacuum leaks can cause the engine to run lean because they allow extra air into the engine, which can upset the air/fuel ratio. You can check for vacuum leaks by using a smoke machine or a spray bottle with carburetor cleaner. Spray the cleaner around the vacuum lines and intake manifold while the engine is running. If the engine's idle speed increases, it means there's a leak, as the cleaner is being sucked into the leak. You can also listen for hissing sounds or look for discolored hoses, which might indicate a leak. If you find a leak, repair it as soon as possible to prevent further issues. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
